The new species differs from
S. melanogaster
by having paravertebral light bands running from nuchal collar reaching behind the parietal region (not forming continuous paravertebral light bands from nuchal collar to the parietal region in
S. melanogaster
); having white marks on center or edges of head scales and postoccipital region (lacking in
S. melanogaster
); having 37–43 scales at midbody (
S. melanogaster
with 31–46 scale rows); maximum SVL for both sexes is 105 mm (
S. melanogaster
